# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   For an app, this is usually fine to prevent git tracking.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you want to keep lock files out, you can uncomment this.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#   pdm.lock
#   pdm.toml database/

